#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:5
msgid "Reading between the lines"
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:9
msgid "Contribute your perspective"
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:11
msgid ""
"Have you had an experience of successfully reading between the lines - or"
" failing to?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:13
msgid ":ref:`How to contribute <contribute>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:16
msgid ""
"Practise looking more deeply, from what people say to what they really "
"need."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:17
msgid ""
"You probably realise that throughout life, what people communicate "
"shouldn't only be taken at face-value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:19
msgid ""
"Learning to identify what really matters from what they say matters is a "
"valuable skill (and therefore it requires practice)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:21
msgid ""
"It applies when job-seeking too. If you are able to look beyond what "
"people say to the deeper needs they are trying to express, you'll give "
"yourself more opportunities for success."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:25
msgid "Asks, wants and needs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:27
msgid ""
"A colleague for example, or a job description, might ask for something. "
"Take that seriously: listen carefully, and pay attention to what job "
"descriptions say."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:29
msgid ""
"But be aware that **what they ask for is not necessarily what they want, "
"and what they want is not necessarily what they need**. So use your "
"judgement, imagination and insight too."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:31
msgid ""
"Ask yourself - or even ask *them*, if you have the opportunity - *why* "
"they want it. And when they say they want something, ask why they *need* "
"it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:33
msgid ""
"You will often get interesting and revealing answers, that show you extra"
" options and opportunities, and even open doors that seemed to be closed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:37
msgid "Example: your manager"
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:39
msgid ""
"Let's say your manager says: \"I want a daily meeting with progress "
"reports from *everyone* on the xxx project!\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:43 ../../between-the-lines.rst:75
msgid "When they ask for something, consider what they really want."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:45
msgid ""
"What they're asking for is clear. Ask yourself: is that really want they "
"*want*? It certainly sounds like your manager wants to be kept closely "
"up-to-date with progress. They want to know what each person is doing. "
"It's not so clear that the *meeting* is really what matters here (and "
"quite likely your manager has quite enough meetings in their diary "
"anyway)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:49 ../../between-the-lines.rst:83
msgid "Then, think about what they actually *need*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:51
msgid ""
"Why would your manager want to know what each person is doing? Why is "
"being aware of progress at that level so important? Ask yourself: does it"
" seem appropriate for a manager to have that level of oversight?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:53
msgid ""
"If not, you might conclude that some anxiety is at work. Perhaps your "
"manager feels that there is a lack of accountability for progress in the "
"team, or that planning has been slack, and so the only way to judge "
"progress is by watching it very closely."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:55
msgid "You can ask about this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:57
msgid ""
"Would it help if I were to provide a daily written summary of activities "
"and outcomes, and if there are any blockers, to make sure to let you know"
" straight away? Perhaps then you wouldn't need to find a slot for a daily"
" meeting just for this project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:59
msgid ""
"That's an appropriate way to question a manager's decision. It suggests "
"an alternative and offers to take responsibility for making it work. Or:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:61
msgid ""
"I think it would also help if we had a more concrete plan, with a "
"timeline for interim delivery of the key dependencies. I did one for "
"project yyy. I made a draft for this one too - would you like to see it?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:63
msgid ""
"Again, this demonstrates initiative and a positive attitude towards a "
"situation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:65
msgid ""
"In the end, it might be that in fact your manager really *does* want to "
"see everyone daily (perhaps they want to assess the team's performance "
"and professional communication skills), but the important thing is for "
"you to get into the habit of **thinking beyond the immediate ask, to "
"thinking about what really matters and why**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:69
msgid "Example: a job description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:71
msgid ""
"Suppose that a job description demands \"three years' Python web agency "
"experience\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:77
msgid ""
"They *asked for* \"three years' Python web agency experience\". Perhaps "
"you have that, or not. Either way, think about what it says about what "
"they *want*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:79
msgid ""
"They want evidence of Python web experience, almost certainly. And most "
"likely they *want* someone who has proven ability to deal with customer "
"requests, deadlines and so on - because those are the kind of things "
"someone who works for an agency has to be able to do. In that case, you "
"might be able to do those things, even if you can't show precisely the "
"agency experience what they asked for."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:85
msgid ""
"Very often, prospective employers want proof and evidence. They want "
"signs that you are going to have the right skills, abilities and "
"attitudes in the job. But, perhaps there are other things that could show"
" you have what they *need*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:87
msgid ""
"*Why* do they want the things they want? What needs do you see revealed? "
"What else do you have that could be evidence you will be able to meet the"
" needs?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:89
msgid ""
"In this particular case, perhaps you conclude that they want evidence of "
"Python web experience, and of ability to work with customers' needs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:91
msgid ""
"Reading between the lines, listening carefully how they talk about it, "
"you might come to the conclusion that what they really *need* is someone "
"who is good at coming up with pragmatic prototypes, quickly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:93
msgid ""
"Get used to asking questions inspired by what you think you are hearing. "
"Good questions unlock hidden treasure. If you ask a question based on an "
"insightful conclusion, people will often reward it with very concrete "
"information: \"That's right! Quick prototyping is exactly the kind of "
"thing we'll need.\" Then they reveal that they'll need more people on a "
"big Django project that is expected to go through several phases of "
"development, with a customer whose own plans are subject to change."
msgstr ""

#: ../../between-the-lines.rst:95
msgid "And that gives you something else you can talk about and show."
msgstr ""

